description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you looking for an exciting opportunity to grow and develop as a Physiotherapist with the training and support that you need to become one of the best?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A permanent post has become available across Central Chesterfield . On occassions you may be required to cover other teams across North East Derbyshire/Dronfield and Chesterfield East according to patient need.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer the opportunity to work within a busy Integrated Community Service alongside Occupational Therapists, Nurses, and Adult Care staff, providing high-quality, evidenced-based therapy for people in the community or in our Beds with Care Units.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role involves both rapid response to prevent hospital admission or facilitate discharge and rehabilitation to optimise functional independence as well as undertaking visits within the Community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a full preceptorship programme for those who are newly qualified or new to community and we provide training and supervision alongside a robust appraisal system to support development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is suitable for newly qualified or more experienced Band 5 Physiotherapist.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ability to meet the travel requirements of the post is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Josie Newton, Integrated Community Team Leader&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Josie.newton2@nhs.net, 07791610558&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jane Saunby 07747780822&lt;/p&gt;
